I don't care who your Father is,

1332
01:05:58,087 --> 01:06:00,356
now you get your
lazy ass in gear,

1333
01:06:00,356 --> 01:06:01,991
get the right film off the truck

1334
01:06:01,991 --> 01:06:04,827
and loaded in five
or you're fired.

1335
01:06:06,662 --> 01:06:07,563
- [Man] Okay, let's rehearse it!

1336
01:06:07,563 --> 01:06:08,497
Let's go, come on!

1337
01:06:10,967 --> 01:06:12,468
- [Michael] Would you
look at this picture?

1338
01:06:12,468 --> 01:06:14,036
Is this not the
most beautiful baby

1339
01:06:14,036 --> 01:06:14,971
you've ever seen
in your whole life?

1340
01:06:14,971 --> 01:06:17,273
- [Man] I wanna see that face.

1341
01:06:17,273 --> 01:06:18,841
- [Michael] Look
at that face huh?

1342
01:06:18,841 --> 01:06:20,676
Look at her, gorgeous.

1343
01:06:20,676 --> 01:06:21,811
- You do a lot of things well,

1344
01:06:21,811 --> 01:06:22,712
but I think this is the best.

1345
01:06:22,712 --> 01:06:23,779
You make great babies.

1346
01:06:23,779 --> 01:06:25,047
- Well I pick great Mama's.

1347
01:06:25,047 --> 01:06:26,215
That's the trick.

1348
01:06:26,215 --> 01:06:27,616
Cindy had this
baby, look at that,

1349
01:06:27,616 --> 01:06:30,152
without a hitch and
she looks really great.

1350
01:06:30,152 --> 01:06:32,388
I got beautiful girls
and I have never

1351
01:06:32,388 --> 01:06:33,990
been happier in my whole life.

1352
01:06:33,990 --> 01:06:35,758
Never been happier!

1353
01:06:35,758 --> 01:06:36,759
Look at this, whoa!

1354
01:06:36,759 --> 01:06:37,693
Hi, hi, hi!

1355
01:06:40,062 --> 01:06:43,032
(rain pouring)

1356
01:06:43,032 --> 01:06:43,866
- [Mike] Hey.

1357
01:06:46,502 --> 01:06:49,005
- I didn't see
your car out front.

1358
01:06:49,005 --> 01:06:50,973
- [Mike] I took a
walk, I had to think.

1359
01:06:54,944 --> 01:06:57,947
How does a man trade in
one family for another

1360
01:06:57,947 --> 01:06:58,781
again and again?

1361
01:07:05,454 --> 01:07:09,291
"Hey, these kids are
getting too damn old.

1362
01:07:09,291 --> 01:07:11,861
"I'll make some younger
ones that can't talk back."

1363
01:07:16,465 --> 01:07:20,136
You know, I used to feel sorry
for my step-brother Josh.

1364
01:07:20,136 --> 01:07:21,470
(somber music)
Now I am Josh.

1365
01:07:23,439 --> 01:07:25,941
How does a man leave his family

1366
01:07:25,941 --> 01:07:27,343
and not even say he's sorry?

1367
01:07:28,511 --> 01:07:29,945
- I don't know.
(thunder rumbling)

1368
01:07:29,945 --> 01:07:32,114
Hell, this whole thing
could be eating him up too.

1369
01:07:32,114 --> 01:07:35,251
- Every rule Dad
taught us, he's broken.

1370
01:07:35,251 --> 01:07:37,319
He's lied, he's cheated--

1371
01:07:37,319 --> 01:07:38,354
- Who doesn't?

1372
01:07:38,354 --> 01:07:40,322
Come on, let's go inside.

1373
01:07:40,322 --> 01:07:42,425
- Hey, maybe my childhood
was an illusion.

1374
01:07:44,026 --> 01:07:46,562
Maybe it was just a
movie Dad ran, right?

1375
01:07:48,798 --> 01:07:49,832
I made it all up.

1376
01:07:53,803 --> 01:07:54,637
Take me home.

1377
01:07:55,971 --> 01:07:57,540
- Where is home these days?

1378
01:08:08,284 --> 01:08:10,553
Hey, you're wasted,
get back in the car!

1379
01:08:10,553 --> 01:08:11,487
- No!

1380
01:08:11,487 --> 01:08:13,155
I told ya, I'm going home!

1381
01:08:13,155 --> 01:08:14,356
- Come on Mike!

1382
01:08:14,356 --> 01:08:15,224
You don't even
live here anymore!

1383
01:08:20,763 --> 01:08:22,298
Hey, I'm leaving Mike!

1384
01:08:22,298 --> 01:08:23,799
(door banging)

1385
01:08:23,799 --> 01:08:26,302
(dog barking)

1386
01:08:27,803 --> 01:08:29,472
Hey, this is it Mike!

1387
01:08:29,472 --> 01:08:31,240
Get in or I'm leaving!

1388
01:08:36,779 --> 01:08:39,048
(door banging)

1389
01:08:39,048 --> 01:08:41,083
- [Homeowner] Who is it?

1390
01:08:41,083 --> 01:08:41,984
- I grew up here.

1391
01:08:42,885 --> 01:08:44,120
I wanna look around.

1392
01:08:44,120 --> 01:08:45,855
- You go away before
I call the police!

1393
01:08:47,189 --> 01:08:48,824
- No, I just wanna
see my old room!

1394
01:08:48,824 --> 01:08:50,960
- [Homeowner] Hey, I'm
gonna call the cops!

1395
01:08:51,994 --> 01:08:54,597
(somber music)

1396
01:09:08,110 --> 01:09:11,013
(thunder rumbling)

1397
01:09:21,657 --> 01:09:23,325
- I need you Father.

1398
01:09:24,960 --> 01:09:26,061
I need you.

1399
01:09:37,006 --> 01:09:38,607
- There's some of you
that are here today

1400
01:09:38,607 --> 01:09:40,643
and you realize there
must be more to life

1401
01:09:40,643 --> 01:09:43,179
than just barely getting by,

1402
01:09:43,179 --> 01:09:44,847
and you wanna change.

1403
01:09:44,847 --> 01:09:47,983
I want every head bowed
and every eye closed.

1404
01:09:47,983 --> 01:09:52,087
And some of you need to receive
the Lord into your life.

1405
01:09:52,087 --> 01:09:55,891
If that's you, if you
want that change today,

1406
01:09:55,891 --> 01:09:58,294
I want you to lift
your hand right now.

1407
01:09:59,762 --> 01:10:04,533
And by that you're saying
"Yes God, change my life."

1408
01:10:23,686 --> 01:10:25,287
So you editing all weekend or?

1409
01:10:27,122 --> 01:10:29,391
- [Michael] Nope,
moving this weekend.

1410
01:10:30,926 --> 01:10:32,394
- Moving?

1411
01:10:32,394 --> 01:10:33,229
- Yeah.

1412
01:10:34,363 --> 01:10:36,031
Cindy found a bigger
house in Malibu.

1413
01:10:37,499 --> 01:10:40,102
Yeah, this way she
can ride her horses

1414
01:10:40,102 --> 01:10:42,538
and I can get back
into playing tennis.

1415
01:10:42,538 --> 01:10:44,039
Kids can have a pool to swim in.

1416
01:10:44,039 --> 01:10:44,940
- [Man] Mr. Landon!

1417
01:10:46,075 --> 01:10:47,476
- Yeah!

1418
01:10:47,476 --> 01:10:49,044
My guest from
Make-A-Wish is here.

1419
01:10:49,044 --> 01:10:49,845
Enjoy.

1420
01:10:51,614 --> 01:10:52,448
Hey!

1421
01:10:52,448 --> 01:10:53,949
Welcome to the set!

1422
01:10:53,949 --> 01:10:56,385
- Glad to see you're still
keeping it simple Dad.

1423
01:10:56,385 --> 01:10:57,453
- Hi.

1424
01:10:57,453 --> 01:10:58,420
- Karen.

1425
01:10:58,420 --> 01:10:59,388
Look, you look beautiful.

1426
01:10:59,388 --> 01:11:00,556
- Thanks!
- Look at you!

1427
01:11:01,924 --> 01:11:03,092
- [Michael] Come on, I
want you to meet everybody.

1428
01:11:03,092 --> 01:11:04,760
Hey Dad, how are you?

1429
01:11:05,661 --> 01:11:07,196
- This show's great for all the

1430
01:11:07,196 --> 01:11:08,897
screwed up families out there.

1431
01:11:08,897 --> 01:11:10,866
Which is every family I know.

1432
01:11:10,866 --> 01:11:12,334
- Not mine.

1433
01:11:12,334 --> 01:11:15,204
My family's always been there
for me when I needed them.

1434
01:11:15,204 --> 01:11:18,507
You know, my parents,
they are so much in love,

1435
01:11:18,507 --> 01:11:20,209
it's really wonderful
to see them.

1436
01:11:25,814 --> 01:11:26,649
- Hi.

1437
01:11:28,050 --> 01:11:30,986
(slow paced music)

1438
01:11:38,927 --> 01:11:40,929
You know what was amazing?

1439
01:11:40,929 --> 01:11:43,532
Hearing you talk about
your family the other day.

1440
01:11:43,532 --> 01:11:44,933
Reminded me of my childhood.

1441
01:11:46,135 --> 01:11:47,636
I knew if there
was a pretty face

1442
01:11:47,636 --> 01:11:49,772
behind that voice,
I had to meet you.

1443
01:11:49,772 --> 01:11:51,640
- So what took you so long?

1444
01:11:51,640 --> 01:11:52,474
- Two weeks?

1445
01:11:52,474 --> 01:11:54,243
Two weeks is long?

1446
01:11:54,243 --> 01:11:56,478
- It seemed like forever to me.

1447
01:11:56,478 --> 01:11:58,947
- [Mike] Well, your
face wasn't that pretty.

1448
01:11:58,947 --> 01:12:00,215
- Hey.

1449
01:12:00,215 --> 01:12:01,016
- It was gorgeous.

1450
01:12:04,320 --> 01:12:06,121
I guess I just had
to find my nerve.

1451
01:12:15,464 --> 01:12:17,433
I found my nerve,
lost my vision.

1452
01:12:17,433 --> 01:12:19,001
- How's that?

1453
01:12:19,001 --> 01:12:20,569
- We fogged up my glasses.

1454
01:12:20,569 --> 01:12:23,238
(both laughing)

1455
01:12:28,711 --> 01:12:30,379
(both screaming)

1456
01:12:30,379 --> 01:12:31,213
Oh my God!

1457
01:12:34,783 --> 01:12:37,786
(people chattering)

1458
01:12:39,054 --> 01:12:40,522
Here you go Dad.

1459
01:12:40,522 --> 01:12:41,590
- Hey, thank you Son.

1460
01:12:41,590 --> 01:12:42,524
- No problem.

1461
01:12:42,524 --> 01:12:43,792
(baby crying)

1462
01:12:43,792 --> 01:12:45,828
- Can you imagine
living down here?

1463
01:12:45,828 --> 01:12:47,329
I mean think about it.

1464
01:12:47,329 --> 01:12:49,765
Trying to raise a family
under these circumstances.

1465
01:12:52,000 --> 01:12:54,169
- I don't know how they do it.

1466
01:12:54,169 --> 01:12:55,003
- I don't either.

1467
01:12:59,141 --> 01:13:01,243
- You know Sheree, the
girl I've been seeing?

1468
01:13:01,243 --> 01:13:02,077
- Yeah.

1469
01:13:03,379 --> 01:13:05,781
- I've asked her to marry me.

1470
01:13:07,282 --> 01:13:08,117
- You're kidding!

1471
01:13:10,185 --> 01:13:12,654
Well how long you
been seeing her Son?

1472
01:13:12,654 --> 01:13:13,489
- Over a year.

1473
01:13:14,823 --> 01:13:16,291
The wedding's in December.

1474
01:13:16,291 --> 01:13:17,126
- December?

1475
01:13:21,029 --> 01:13:22,431
Congratulations Son.

1476
01:13:22,431 --> 01:13:23,265
- [Mike] Thanks Dad.

1477
01:13:23,265 --> 01:13:25,667
- Come here, come on.

1478
01:13:25,667 --> 01:13:27,770
Of course, you know, if I
had to do it all over again,

1479
01:13:27,770 --> 01:13:31,373
I'd probably wait,
a little older.

1480
01:13:31,373 --> 01:13:33,008
You know, live a little.

1481
01:13:33,008 --> 01:13:34,343
It's like Hemingway said,

1482
01:13:34,343 --> 01:13:36,612
"True love always ends badly,"

1483
01:13:36,612 --> 01:13:38,013
unless both people
are fortunate enough

1484
01:13:38,013 --> 01:13:39,481
to die in the same accident.

1485
01:13:39,481 --> 01:13:41,750
But they're just chasing misery
and they're gonna catch it.

1486
01:13:46,889 --> 01:13:48,157
- [Woman] Can we get
craft services over here!

1487
01:13:48,157 --> 01:13:50,592
- Come on, I'm
kidding, I'm kidding!

1488
01:13:52,728 --> 01:13:53,529
Lighten up!

1489
01:13:53,529 --> 01:13:54,730
Hey Andy!

1490
01:13:54,730 --> 01:13:56,665
My 23-year-old Son's
getting married!

1491
01:13:56,665 --> 01:13:58,100
- [Andy] That's wonderful!

1492
01:14:03,639 --> 01:14:04,706
- Sorry I'm late.

1493
01:14:07,743 --> 01:14:10,579
So, you know the tent
people just informed me

1494
01:14:10,579 --> 01:14:13,182
that they won't guarantee
against leaks in December.

1495
01:14:14,049 --> 01:14:15,684
So I think we should move the

1496
01:14:15,684 --> 01:14:16,952
reception to a hotel.

1497
01:14:17,886 --> 01:14:18,787
What do you think?

1498
01:14:21,890 --> 01:14:25,060
- Who wants to hassle
with weather and tents?

1499
01:14:25,060 --> 01:14:25,994
I think we should wait.

1500
01:14:25,994 --> 01:14:27,162
You know, not force this.

1501
01:14:28,730 --> 01:14:30,065
- Hassle?

1502
01:14:30,065 --> 01:14:30,999
Force this?

1503
01:14:32,000 --> 01:14:33,569
How can you even
say those words?

1504
01:14:33,569 --> 01:14:34,670
What's happened?

1505
01:14:34,670 --> 01:14:35,504
- Nothing.

1506
01:14:37,940 --> 01:14:39,708
- Not good enough
Mike, talk to me.

1507
01:14:40,876 --> 01:14:41,710
- I don't know.

1508
01:14:44,480 --> 01:14:45,681
I was talking to my Dad--

1509
01:14:45,681 --> 01:14:47,683
- Ugh, you're not
marrying your Father,

1510
01:14:47,683 --> 01:14:49,418
you're marrying me.

1511
01:14:49,418 --> 01:14:50,552
- Sheree, wait.

1512
01:14:53,088 --> 01:14:55,157
And you know it's not
because I don't love ya.

1513
01:14:56,024 --> 01:14:57,292
Because I do.

1514
01:14:59,294 --> 01:15:00,295
Just that I'm scared.

1515
01:15:02,898 --> 01:15:05,234
I'm scared that I'm gonna
end up just like him.

1516
01:15:06,568 --> 01:15:08,904
You know, and leave you
and not really know why.

1517
01:15:08,904 --> 01:15:11,940
- Mike, you recognize your fear,

1518
01:15:11,940 --> 01:15:13,175
we're talking about it,

1519
01:15:14,309 --> 01:15:15,711
the cycle's already broken.

1520
01:15:18,413 --> 01:15:19,248
- You're right.

1521
01:15:21,850 --> 01:15:23,018
I'm not like my Father.

1522
01:15:25,754 --> 01:15:27,789
I don't need to look
to him for approval.

1523
01:15:32,194 --> 01:15:33,562
I just need to look inside.

1524
01:15:36,064 --> 01:15:37,432
And inside I find us.

1525
01:15:42,070 --> 01:15:44,339
(light gentle music)

1526
01:15:44,339 --> 01:15:45,173
(camera shutters)

1527
01:15:45,173 --> 01:15:46,308
- That's good.

1528
01:15:46,308 --> 01:15:47,309
That's fine.

1529
01:15:48,810 --> 01:15:51,179
Hey Son, congratulations Son.

1530
01:15:51,179 --> 01:15:52,014
- Thanks.

1531
01:15:54,283 --> 01:15:56,184
- Awe, she's a beaut Michael.

1532
01:15:57,352 --> 01:16:00,022
She's kind, she's pretty.

1533
01:16:02,658 --> 01:16:04,993
I think you two are gonna build,

1534
01:16:04,993 --> 01:16:05,827
build a fine,

1535
01:16:08,764 --> 01:16:09,932
fine life together Son.

1536
01:16:12,134 --> 01:16:15,404
I think you finally got
everything you need.

1537
01:16:15,404 --> 01:16:17,072
- Thanks Dad.

1538
01:16:17,072 --> 01:16:19,675
I couldn't agree with you more.

1539
01:16:22,511 --> 01:16:23,412
- All right, come on.

1540
01:16:23,412 --> 01:16:25,147
Let's get some food.

1541
01:16:26,648 --> 01:16:28,150
How about a drink.

1542
01:16:29,551 --> 01:16:30,719
- Let's dance.

1543
01:16:32,521 --> 01:16:35,857
♪ Happy anniversary to us

1544
01:16:35,857 --> 01:16:40,095
♪ Happy anniversary to us

1545
01:16:40,095 --> 01:16:40,929
- Wow.

1546
01:16:42,364 --> 01:16:44,433
Oh, no bubbly for me.

1547
01:16:44,433 --> 01:16:46,101
- But this is a
special occasion.

1548
01:16:47,069 --> 01:16:48,337
- Doctor's orders.

1549
01:16:52,908 --> 01:16:54,710
- What?
(Sheree giggling)

1550
01:16:54,710 --> 01:16:55,544
What?

1551
01:16:57,179 --> 01:16:58,413
Are you, are you kidding?

1552
01:16:58,413 --> 01:17:00,816
- Congratulations Daddy.

1553
01:17:00,816 --> 01:17:01,883
- I'm gonna be a Dad.

1554
01:17:02,718 --> 01:17:03,552
Oh my God!

1555
01:17:04,786 --> 01:17:05,621
Oh my God.

1556
01:17:07,923 --> 01:17:09,725
- Isn't it wonderful?

1557
01:17:09,725 --> 01:17:10,559
- I love you so much.

1558
01:17:10,559 --> 01:17:11,393
- I love you.

1559
01:17:12,494 --> 01:17:15,330
(Sheree giggling)

1560
01:17:16,365 --> 01:17:17,199
Mom!

1561
01:17:18,433 --> 01:17:21,103
Here's your first look
at your new grandchild.

1562
01:17:21,103 --> 01:17:22,571
You're gonna love this.

1563
01:17:22,571 --> 01:17:24,373
You can't believe how
active this little one is.

1564
01:17:26,241 --> 01:17:27,843
What's wrong?
(solemn music)

1565
01:17:27,843 --> 01:17:29,344
- [Lynn] Your Dad called.

1566
01:17:29,344 --> 01:17:32,347
He'd like all the kids to
meet him down at the house.

1567
01:17:32,347 --> 01:17:33,181
- [Mike] Why?

1568
01:17:34,716 --> 01:17:36,418
- [Lynn] Just call
your Dad honey.

1569
01:17:36,418 --> 01:17:38,654
- [Mike] Mom, just tell me.

1570
01:17:41,456 --> 01:17:43,058
- [Lynn] Your Dad's
been diagnosed with

1571
01:17:43,058 --> 01:17:45,127
inoperable pancreatic cancer

1572
01:17:45,127 --> 01:17:47,195
and it doesn't look good.

1573
01:17:49,264 --> 01:17:51,767
(Mike grunts)

1574
01:18:01,143 --> 01:18:02,744
- All right, here are the rules.

1575
01:18:04,279 --> 01:18:05,347
I want no tears.

1576
01:18:07,149 --> 01:18:08,684
I want no sad faces.

1577
01:18:10,285 --> 01:18:12,387
I want no phony
happy faces either.

1578
01:18:14,056 --> 01:18:16,058
I'm gonna call a press
conference and tell everybody

1579
01:18:16,058 --> 01:18:20,796
that I'm not just gonna lie
down and let this happen to me.

1580
01:18:22,464 --> 01:18:26,168
And I want life
for the little ones

1581
01:18:27,569 --> 01:18:28,837
to be as normal as possible,

1582
01:18:28,837 --> 01:18:32,040
so you bigger kids,
I want you to limit

1583
01:18:32,040 --> 01:18:34,109
your visitations
to weekends only.

1584
01:18:36,344 --> 01:18:37,179
Okay?

1585
01:18:42,017 --> 01:18:44,619
(somber music)

1586
01:19:08,677 --> 01:19:09,978
- Breaker, breaker!

1587
01:19:09,978 --> 01:19:11,646
I'm looking for help!

1588
01:19:11,646 --> 01:19:13,515
I need alternative cancer cures!

1589
01:19:15,083 --> 01:19:16,551
I desperately need a cure!

1590
01:19:16,551 --> 01:19:17,385
Come back!

1591
01:19:23,158 --> 01:19:23,992
Breaker! Breaker!

1592
