Honey, your Dad's a
very complicated man.

1653
01:22:18,300 --> 01:22:19,868
- But why?

1654
01:22:19,868 --> 01:22:20,936
Why did he leave us?

1655
01:22:24,406 --> 01:22:25,874
- I don't know for sure, but,

1656
01:22:27,709 --> 01:22:28,944
do you remember how you felt

1657
01:22:28,944 --> 01:22:31,279
when you felt like
your Dad failed us?

1658
01:22:31,279 --> 01:22:32,247
How you fell apart?

1659
01:22:33,581 --> 01:22:35,984
Imagine that happened to
you at eight years old.

1660
01:22:37,619 --> 01:22:40,055
Your Dad told me
this story once.

1661
01:22:40,055 --> 01:22:41,523
It was about his eighth birthday

1662
01:22:41,523 --> 01:22:45,193
and he'd asked his Mom
for weeks to have a party.

1663
01:22:46,428 --> 01:22:48,530
So they sent out
the invitations,

1664
01:22:48,530 --> 01:22:49,965
they decorated the house,

1665
01:22:49,965 --> 01:22:54,869
and an hour before the guests
were supposed to arrive,

1666
01:22:55,737 --> 01:22:56,571
she canceled it.

1667
01:22:58,940 --> 01:23:01,109
She said she didn't like
eight year old boys.

1668
01:23:04,245 --> 01:23:08,283
She never celebrated him
in that house ever again.

1669
01:23:08,283 --> 01:23:09,784
He felt like he didn't exist.

1670
01:23:11,953 --> 01:23:13,688
It nearly destroyed him,

1671
01:23:13,688 --> 01:23:17,792
and I think the thing
that hurt him the most

1672
01:23:17,792 --> 01:23:21,730
was that he, he couldn't
talk to his Father about it.

1673
01:23:23,398 --> 01:23:26,835
- That's why he wrote all those
shows about happy families.

1674
01:23:29,270 --> 01:23:31,940
Because that's what he wished
his childhood had been like.

1675
01:23:34,476 --> 01:23:36,444
- Don't make the
same mistake Michael.

1676
01:23:38,713 --> 01:23:40,782
You talk to him.

1677
01:23:40,782 --> 01:23:41,616
- I'm afraid to.

1678
01:23:44,319 --> 01:23:46,354
I don't even know how
to make him listen.

1679
01:23:50,492 --> 01:23:53,561
- Maybe you could
write him a letter.

1680
01:23:54,763 --> 01:23:56,398
Try.

1681
